SIMPLE: housebreaking
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Housebreaking
<hw>House"break`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of breaking open
and entering, with a felonious purpose, the dwelling house of another,
whether done by day or night. See <er>Burglary</er>, and <cref>To break
a house</cref>, under <er>Break</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>housebroken</ent>⟦br⟧
